{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-09T15:22:14.794957826Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"1. **`file(...)` wrapper not unwrapped** — The DSL parser stores prompt values as `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")` (literal string with the `file()` wrapper). The handler tried to use this directly as a file path, so `os.ReadFile` failed.","timestamp":"2026-03-09T15:22:14.79496022Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-09T15:22:14.79497061Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"2. **Wrong config key names** — The handler checked for `command` and `script` config keys, but the DSL uses `run` for script steps.","timestamp":"2026-03-09T15:22:14.794972474Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-09T15:22:14.794979787Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"**Changes:**","timestamp":"2026-03-09T15:22:14.794981591Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"- `handler.go`: Added `extractFilePath()` helper to unwrap `file(\"...\")` references. Changed the handler to check for `run` config key and use `extractFilePath` on both `prompt` and `run` values.","timestamp":"2026-03-09T15:22:14.794983444Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"- `project_detail.html`: Updated the drawer to display the `run` config key (instead of `command`/`script`) and unwrap `file(...)` for cleaner display.","timestamp":"2026-03-09T15:22:14.794987813Z"}
